<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong>: Just a quick question in regards to the removal of Angband Abilities from ToME. Do modifiers to stealth from ego-items and the like affect the stealth SKILL in the same way (+1 to stealth = +1000 to the Stealth Skill)?  <p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: The effects of those items are unchanged. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong>: So the abilities still exist? Are they just being removed in the sense of Race and Class modifiers, with their internal use remaining?  
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: There are two major skill-related changes from ToME 2.2 to 2.3.  The first is more of a bugfix:  a temporary thing put into ToME way back before 2.0 came out was replaced.  Before 2.3, real skills had different effects for different classes.  That's no longer the case. 
</p>
<p>
The second is a change to the races.  In 2.2, races have innate modifers to those Angband "skills".  In 2.3, those are gone and replaced with modifiers to real skills. 
</p>
<p>
So the result is that the player no longer has to worry about the Angband "skills."  All character bonuses and penalties are to real skills. 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong>: So do the Angband abilities still work? (i.e. your chance of a melee hit is based off your "Fighting" ability rather than Combat/Weaponmastery) Are the game mechanics going to hang completely off the skill system, is, I suppose, my ultimate question...  <p>
 <strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Players don't need to know or care about the internal legacy code in ToME.  If you want an answer for a developer, let me know. 
</p>
<p>
 <strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong>: Well I wouldn't class myself as a developer, but I'd still be interested to know. (if spoily, you could PM me on the ToME forums).  
</p>
<p>
 <strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: To see the raw, technical details of the relationship between the real skills and the internal stuff, see the function <tt>void&nbsp;calc_bonuses(bool&nbsp;silent)</tt> in the file <tt>xtra1.c</tt>.  Lines like <tt>p_ptr-&gt;skill_sav&nbsp;+=&nbsp;adj_wis_sav[get_skill_scale(SKILL_SPIRITUALITY,&nbsp;37)];</tt> show the complete relationship. 
</p>

    </ul>


<p>
<strong><a href="./ErisDiscordia">ErisDiscordia</a></strong>: Oh, wow, so no more e.g. 25% reduction to Spirituality's effect on saving throw for mage classes relative to priest classes, x% reduction to Combat's effect for mages relative to warriors, etc.? I suppose it solves a lot of problems at once -- helps with making fighter-mages playable, helps keep the boost to Spirituality's importance from vastly boosting the relative power of Priest classes, etc. 
</p>
<p>
BTW how do the subzero ("-16" and so on) starting skills work, I mean things like the awful starting stealth of some races? Or do they not work yet and just get set to zero? I seem to remember raising a 2.3 character's skill in something and it staying at zero for a while... if so, I assume some way of actually expressing the negatives in the Gain Skills screen will be added before release. 
</p>
<p>
I also ran into some REALLY buggy behavior recently when editing some character's stealth -- things like skill points having no effect when added, then not being returnable using the left arrow key. I think there might have been some crashes in there too. I really oughta try to repro that on the latest build.... 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: They are suppsed to just work as negative skills.  As of right now they seem to, in fact.  If a penalty drops a skill below 0, it must be increased multiple times before it gets above 0. 
</p>
